thread.title: After the March, Student Activists Look to Midterm Elections

author: Nicole Hong
title: After the March, Student Activists Look to Midterm Elections
text:
Hundreds of thousands of young people around the world marched this weekend to demand stricter gun laws in the U.S. Now, student activists are turning to pushing for change at the polls in November.
Students say the March for Our Lives, led by the survivors of last monthâ€™s school shooting that killed 17 people in Parkland, Fla., is a starting point to build momentum ahead of the midterm elections.
